Process clustering results into evaluation metrics, rentention, singleton retention, fraction, singleton fraction

setwd("~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering")
files<-list.files(path="~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering",pattern="n*.tsv",full.names = T, recursive = FALSE)
datalist<-list()

result1=NULL
result2=NULL
#outcoor=NULL
for (j in 1:length(files)) {
  q<-read.table(files[j],header = TRUE,sep="\t")
  files[j]<-gsub(".tsv","",files[j])
  files[j]<-gsub(".*n_","",files[j])
  
  method<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[5]
  threshold<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[1]
  
    entropy<-q %>%
    group_by(cluster,truth) %>%
    summarise(number = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate(sum=sum(number)) %>%
    mutate(shannon=diversity(number,index="shannon")) %>%
    arrange(desc(shannon))  %>%
    ungroup()
  
  single<-q %>%
    group_by(cluster,truth) %>%
    summarise(number = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate(sum=sum(number)) %>%
    filter(sum==1) %>%
    ungroup()
  
  
  #####singleton retention#######
  
  sing_reten=nrow(single)/nrow(q)
  
  #####singleton fraction ### ####
  
  entropysum<-unique(data.frame(entropy$cluster,entropy$shannon))
  sing_fra=nrow(single)/nrow(entropysum)
  
  #####retention none singleton##########
  pure=entropy[entropy$shannon==0,]
  nones_retention=(sum(pure$sum)-nrow(pure[pure$sum==1,]))/nrow(q)
  
  #### fraction none singleton##########
  nones_fraction=(nrow(pure)-nrow(single))/nrow(entropysum)
  
 
  result<-data.frame(method,threshold,sing_reten,nones_retention,sing_fra,nones_fraction)
 colnames(result)<-c("method","threshold","singleton retention","non-singleton retention","singleton fraction","non-singleton fraction")
  
  result1=rbind(result1,result)
}

Transform data into long table

df_long<- melt(result1, id.vars =c("method_threshold"), measure.vars = c("singleton retention","non-singleton retention","singleton fraction","non-singleton fraction"))

colnames(df_long)[which(names(df_long) == "variable")] <- "Evaluation matrix"

Filter each evaluation metrix

singleton_retention <- df_long %>%
  filter(`Evaluation matrix` == "singleton retention")

singleton_fraction <- df_long %>%
  filter(`Evaluation matrix` == "singleton fraction")

none_singleton_retention <- df_long %>%
  filter(`Evaluation matrix` == "non-singleton retention")

none_singleton_fraction <- df_long %>%
  filter(`Evaluation matrix` == "non-singleton fraction")

Comparisons of fractions (singleton VS non-singleton) with different threshold series of each method

df_long_fraction<-rbind(singleton_fraction,none_singleton_fraction)
df_long_retention<-rbind(singleton_retention,none_singleton_retention)



ggplot(df_long_fraction) + geom_segment(data = singleton_fraction,
              aes(x = value, y = method_threshold,
                  yend = none_singleton_fraction$method_threshold, xend =none_singleton_fraction$value), 
              color = "#aeb6bf",
              size = 4.5, #Note that I sized the segment to fit the points
              alpha = .5) +  geom_point(aes(x = value, y = method_threshold, color = `Evaluation matrix`), size = 4, show.legend = TRUE)+
        xlab("Ratio") + ylab("Method with threshold")+ theme_bw()+
           theme(axis.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
        legend.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
        legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
        axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
        strip.text = element_text(face = "bold"))

Check the pure clusters and calculate the maximum distance in the pure clusters

setwd("~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering/pure_clusters/size_100/")
files<-list.files(path="~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering/pure_clusters/size_100",pattern="n*.tsv",full.names = T, recursive = FALSE)
datalist<-list()

res1=NULL
res2=NULL
res3=NULL
#outcoor=NULL
for (j in 1:length(files)) {
  q<-read.table(files[j],header = TRUE,sep="\t")
  files[j]<-gsub(".tsv","",files[j])
  files[j]<-gsub(".*n_","",files[j])
  
  method<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[5]
  threshold<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[1]
  size<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[2]
  
  entropy<-q %>%
    group_by(cluster,truth) %>%
    summarise(number = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate(pure_size=sum(number)) %>%
    mutate(shannon=diversity(number,index="shannon")) %>%
    arrange(desc(shannon))  %>%
        filter(pure_size>1) %>%
    ungroup()
    
   
  pure=entropy[entropy$shannon==0,]
  
  full_pure<-left_join(pure,q,by="cluster")
  
   dimension<- full_pure %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    summarise(hds=unlist(as.list(stringdistmatrix(
      unique(as.character(junction)),unique(as.character(junction)),method = "lv")))) %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate("max_HD"=max(hds)) %>%
    select(-hds) %>%
    distinct() 
  
  pure<-left_join(full_pure,dimension,by="cluster")
   

    pure_sum<-pure %>% 
          distinct(cluster, pure_size, max_HD, truth.x) %>%
          ungroup()
    
    
  pure_sum$method<-method
  res1=rbind(res1,pure_sum)
   
  summary<-pure_sum %>%
           group_by(pure_size) %>%
           count(pure_size,name="frequency")
    
  summary$method<-method
  res2=rbind(res2,summary)
  
  
   length_sum<-pure %>%  count(cluster,junction_length) 
      
   
        
        pure_inf<-pure %>%
           distinct(cluster, pure_size, max_HD, truth.x) %>%
          ungroup()
        
  length_result <-inner_join(pure_inf,length_sum, by="cluster") %>% 
          mutate(result = ifelse(pure_size == n, "pure", "impure"))  
    
  length_result$method<-method
  res3=rbind(res3,length_result)
  
 
  
}

Check the non-pure clusters and calculate the maximum distance in the non-pure clusters

setwd("~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering/pure_clusters/size_100/")
files<-list.files(path="~/Desktop/AnchorClustering_Code/cha9_benchmarking_clustering/pure_clusters/size_100",pattern="n*.tsv",full.names = T, recursive = FALSE)
datalist<-list()

nres1=NULL
nres2=NULL
nres3=NULL
#outcoor=NULL
for (j in 1:length(files)) {
  q<-read.table(files[j],header = TRUE,sep="\t")
  files[j]<-gsub(".tsv","",files[j])
  files[j]<-gsub(".*n_","",files[j])
  
  method<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[5]
  threshold<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[1]
  size<-unlist(strsplit(files[j], split="_"))[2]
  
  entropy<-q %>%
    group_by(cluster,truth) %>%
    summarise(number = n()) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate(total_size=sum(number)) %>%
    mutate(shannon=diversity(number,index="shannon")) %>%
    arrange(desc(shannon))  %>%
        filter(total_size>1) %>%
    ungroup()
    
   
  npure=entropy[entropy$shannon!=0,]
  
  full_npure<-left_join(npure,q,by=c("cluster","truth"))
  
  
   dimension<- full_npure %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    summarise(hds=unlist(as.list(stringdistmatrix(
      unique(as.character(junction)),unique(as.character(junction)),method = "lv")))) %>%
    group_by(cluster) %>%
    mutate("max_HD"=max(hds)) %>%
    select(-hds) %>%
    distinct() 
  
  npure<-left_join(full_npure,dimension,by="cluster")
   
  npure_sum<-npure %>% 
          distinct(cluster, total_size, max_HD, truth) %>%
          ungroup()
    
    
  npure_sum$method<-method
  nres1=rbind(nres1,npure_sum)
   
  summary<-npure_sum %>%
           group_by(total_size) %>%
           count(total_size,name="frequency")
    
  summary$method<-method
  nres2=rbind(nres2,summary)
  
  
   truth_sum<-npure %>%  count(cluster,truth) 
      
   
        
npure_inf<-npure %>%
           distinct(cluster, total_size, max_HD) %>%
          ungroup()
        
  truth_result <-inner_join(npure_inf,truth_sum, by="cluster")
    
  truth_result$method<-method
  nres3=rbind(nres3,truth_result)
  
 
  
}
